OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782501495
OL,3,CHome Office plans to use more military
OL,4,Csites for asylum accommodation
OL,6,FAt the end of March, there were 20,885
OL,7,Fpeople staying in hotels while
OL,8,Fawaiting a decision on their asylum
OL,9,Fclaims down 35% year-on-year from
OL,10,F32,326.
OL,12,FThe total had climbed as high as
OL,13,F56,018 at the end of September 2023.
OL,15,FOn Thursday, Prime Minister Keir
OL,16,FStarmer said that migration had "long
OL,17,Fbeen a cause for concern" and that his
OL,18,Fgovernment have brought those numbers
OL,19,Fdown" and praised the closure of these
OL,20,Fhotels.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
