OL,3,CHome Office plans to use more military
OL,4,Csites for asylum accommodation
OL,6,FBorder security and asylum minister
OL,7,FAlex Norris said: "We promised to
OL,8,Fclose every asylum hotel and hand them
OL,9,Fback to communities, and that is
OL,10,Fexactly what we are doing.
OL,12,F"Twenty more hotels have closed, and
OL,13,Fhotel numbers have more than halved
OL,14,Fsince their peak. Instead, we're
OL,15,Fmoving asylum seekers into ex-military
OL,16,Fsites that are a far cry from the
OL,17,Fhotels the last Government left us
OL,18,Fwith.
OL,26,@oD@SO]tD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782501495
OL,3,CHome Office plans to use more military
OL,4,Csites for asylum accommodation
OL,6,F"This is a system being brought back
OL,7,Funder control ` and we will not stop
OL,8,Funtil the job is done."
OL,10,FHowever, campaigners are already
OL,11,Fobjecting to the announcement.
OL,13,FProf Olga Matthias, of the Linton-on-
OL,14,FOuse Action Group, said: "The decision
OL,15,Fto use the former RAF Linton-on-Ouse
OL,16,FBase for asylum seekers is bonkers.
OL,18,F"It was a ridiculous decision in 2022,
OL,19,Fand that still applies - possibly more
OL,20,Fso, given four years of further
OL,21,Fdeteriorating infrastructure.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@WO]vD@ZOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782501495
OL,3,CHome Office plans to use more military
OL,4,Csites for asylum accommodation
OL,6,F"At least the Conservative government
OL,7,Faccepted, after wasting several
OL,8,Fmillions of taxpayer money, that
OL,9,Fthey'd made a mistake. What this
OL,10,Fgovernment has consistently
OL,11,Fdemonstrated in the last 24 months is
OL,12,Fthat if there is a wrong decision to
OL,13,Fbe made, they will.
OL,15,F"And in the face of valid critique,
OL,16,Finstead of reflection and
OL,17,Freconsideration, they will dig their
OL,18,Fheels in and double down on the error."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
